President Muhammadu Buhari will visit Ogun State on Thursday, January 13, 2022, to inaugurate some of the projects executed by Governor Dapo Abiodun. According to a statement by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Kunle Somorin, the President will be welcomed at the Gateway City Gate Monument Park, Sagamu Interchange, at 10 a.m., where he will commission the first project. The statement added that other projects billed for inauguration by the President include Ijebu Ode/Mojoda/Epe expressway, the 527-unit low- and medium-income Kobape Housing Scheme and 83 duplexes at Kings Court Estate, Oke Mosan, Abeokuta. Invited guests, Somorin indicated in the statement, should be seated at the City Gate by 9.30 a.m., strictly observing all Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) safety protocols.